            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>creamed coconut </strong>roughly<strong> </strong>(if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>and your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[450ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[590ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Trim, then chop your <strong>green beans</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Once the tomato has begun to break down, add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for an initial 8-10 min or until the potatoes are tender</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1649847924870-x200.jpg",
